>>
endobj
341 0 obj
<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /P
/P 178 0 R
/E (Set a minimum AI usage threshold. The data shows that partial adoption  \(between 20% and 30%\) is the riskiest configuration. Teams should either commit to AI or not use it at all. We recommend setting a minimum threshold of 30% AI usage for any AI-assisted engagement.)
/Pg 21 0 R
/K [1]
>>
endobj
342 0 obj
<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /P
/P 178 0 R
/E (Invest in AI training for senior profiles. The gap between junior and senior performance is not just a pricing issue: it is an adoption issue. Juniors leverage AI naturally and effectively; seniors do not. Structured AI training for senior professionals could help close this gap and partially offset their higher cost base.)
/Pg 21 0 R
/K [2]
>>
endobj
343 0 obj
<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /P
/P 178 0 R
/E (Reprice senior profiles on hourly contracts. Senior professionals generate negative margins under the hourly model regardless of how much AI they use. The fix is not to push them to use more AI , it is to move them to a fixed or value-based pricing model where their expertise, not their hours, determines the price.)
/Pg 21 0 R
/K [3]
>>
endobj
